In this article, President Donald Trump proclaims April 2020 as National Child Abuse Prevention Month. He acknowledges the unfortunate reality that many children in the United States experience abuse and neglect, and condemns this behavior. Trump highlights the steps that the government has taken to combat child exploitation, including coordinating efforts to prosecute individuals who exploit children online, supporting at-risk families through treatment programs, and establishing the Voluntary Principles to Counter Online Child Sexual Exploitation and Abuse. The President emphasizes the importance of loving and caring families in protecting children from abuse and neglect. He calls upon all Americans to invest in the lives of children, be aware of their safety and well-being, and support efforts that promote their development.